{
  "texts": [
    "The GEM CR metric needs to identify whether the summary includes a specific section structure.",
    "To accomplish this, we used Stanford CoreNLP to segment the sentences in the generated summary, and then applied sentence-BERT (Reimers & Gurevych, 2019) to compute the cosine similarity between each sentence and the sections of the source article.",
    "The section category with the highest similarity score is then assigned as the corresponding category for each sentence.",
    "In this section, we first report the results of the SFR task, followed by the results of the AR task.",
    "Additionally, to better evaluate the model's performance, we also include the results of human evaluation and ablation experiments."
  ]
}